{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847815001,"sessionID":"ses_2873b7541ffeDi6b2Lu8gh0Fzw","part":{"id":"prt_d78c73710001rQmURPHB4iID2a","messageID":"msg_d78c6fa1a001iJkm56Z1Rfdyte","sessionID":"ses_2873b7541ffeDi6b2Lu8gh0Fzw","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-adb490df39dd4e318fc7859c635eee84","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the Go type structures for `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. This CRD provides a specialized sandbox runtime for code execution environments with enhanced features:\n6: \n7: 1. **Warm Pool Management**: Pre-provisioned sandboxes for low-latency startup\n8: 2. **Authentication Integration**: Support for picod auth mode\n9: 3. **Port Exposure**: HTTP/HTTPS endpoints for code interpreter communication\n10: 4. **Resource Management**: CPU/Memory limits for code execution sandboxes\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: ### In Scope\n15: \n16: | Deliverable | Description |\n17: |-------------|-------------|\n18: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | Type definitions for CodeInterpreter, CodeInterpreterSpec, CodeInterpreterStatus, CodeInterpreterList |\n19: | Supporting types | CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, AuthModeType constants, validation markers |\n20: \n21: ### Type Definitions Required\n22: \n23: #### CodeInterpreter\n24: \n25: ```\n26: CodeInterpreter\n27: ├── Spec\n28: │   ├── Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: ports)\n29: │   ├── Template (*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, JSON: template, required)\n30: │   ├── SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, default: 15m)\n31: │   ├── MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, default: 8h)\n32: │   ├── WarmPoolSize (*int32)\n33: │   └── AuthMode (AuthModeType, default: picod, enum: picod|none)\n34: ├── Status\n35: │   ├── Conditions ([]metav1.Condition)\n36: │   └── Ready (*bool)\n37: └── List: CodeInterpreterList\n38: ```\n39: \n40: #### Supporting Types\n41: \n42: - `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`: Image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, imagePullPolicy, imagePullSecrets\n43: - `AuthModeType`: Enum for picod/none authentication modes\n44: \n45: ### Out of Scope\n46: \n47: - Controller implementation (`pkg/controllers/`)\n48: - Webhook validation logic\n49: - CRD YAML generation (handled by `make gen-crd`)\n50: - client-go code generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n51: - AgentRuntime CRD (handled in AR-001)\n52: \n53: ## Impact Analysis\n54: \n55: ### Upstream Dependencies\n56: \n57: | Dependency | Impact |\n58: |------------|--------|\n59: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required for metav1.ObjectMeta, metav1.Duration, metav1.Condition |\n60: | `k8s.io/api/corev1` | Required for PodSpec elements (EnvVar, PullPolicy, ResourceRequirements) |\n61: \n62: ### Downstream Consumers\n63: \n64: | Consumer | Usage |\n65: |----------|-------|\n66: | `make gen-crd` | Generates CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n67: | `make gen-client` | Generates typed clients, informers, listers |\n68: | Workload Manager | Creates Sandbox/SandboxClaim instances from CodeInterpreter specs |\n69: | Router | Routes code interpreter requests to appropriate sandboxes |\n70: \n71: ## Alternatives Considered\n72: \n73: | Alternative | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n74: |-------------|------|------|----------|\n75: | **Inline Template (corev1.PodSpec)** | Direct reuse of Kubernetes types, familiar API | Too permissive, includes fields not relevant to code interpreters (init containers, volumes, etc.) | Rejected |\n76: | **Separate WarmPool CRD** | Decoupled warm pool lifecycle management | Adds complexity, warm pool is tightly coupled to interpreter spec | Rejected |\n77: | **AuthMode as string (no enum)** | Flexible for future modes | No validation, prone to typos | Rejected - use typed enum |\n78: | **Embed SandboxTemplate from AgentRuntime** | Code reuse, consistency | Different requirements (AgentRuntime uses full PodSpec, CodeInterpreter needs lighter template) | Rejected - use dedicated CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate |\n79: | **Status with multiple condition types** | Rich status reporting | Over-engineering for S-size task | Rejected - keep simple with Conditions + Ready |\n80: \n81: ## Risks\n82: \n83: | Risk | Mitigation |\n84: |------|------------|\n85: | Warm pool size validation | Consider webhook for min/max values |\n86: | AuthMode enum changes | Pin enum values in design doc |\n87: | Status field extensions | Reserve fields for future use |\n88: \n89: ## Implementation Notes\n90: \n91: 1. **Boilerplate**: Use `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` header\n92: 2. **JSON Tags**: camelCase per project conventions\n93: 3. **Kubebuilder Markers**: Apply validation markers for required fields and enums\n94: 4. **Printer Columns**: Add Age column for `kubectl get` output\n95: \n96: ## References\n97: \n98: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n99: - Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n\n(End of file - total 99 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the Go type structures for `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. This CRD provides a specialized sandbox runtime for code execution environments with enhanced features:\n\n1. **Warm Pool Management**: Pre-provisioned sandboxes for low-latency startup\n2. **Authentication Integration**: Support for picod auth mode\n3. **Port Exposure**: HTTP/HTTPS endpoints for code interpreter communication\n4. **Resource Management**: CPU/Memory limits for code execution sandboxes\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | Type definitions for CodeInterpreter, CodeInterpreterSpec, CodeInterpreterStatus, CodeInterpreterList |\n| Supporting types | CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, AuthModeType constants, validation markers |\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775847814994,"end":1775847815000}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847815004,"sessionID":"ses_2873b7541ffeDi6b2Lu8gh0Fzw","part":{"id":"prt_d78c7358c0018bLTRna4mFpV2I","messageID":"msg_d78c6fa1a001iJkm56Z1Rfdyte","sessionID":"ses_2873b7541ffeDi6b2Lu8gh0Fzw","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f1daed5800e944fbb43c54e404e9af78","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the foundational Go type structures for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These types serve as the core data model for AgentCube's sandbox orchestration platform, enabling:\n6: \n7: 1. **Sandbox Template Definition**: Users define pod templates and runtime parameters via CRDs\n8: 2. **Controller Integration**: The workload manager controller uses these types to create/manage `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` resources\n9: 3. **Client Generation**: These types are the source for `k8s.io/code-generator` to produce typed clients, informers, and listers (see `deployment/client-go.md`)\n10: 4. **Helm Chart CRDs**: `controller-gen` generates CRD YAML from these types (see `manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: ### In Scope\n15: \n16: | Deliverable | Description |\n17: |-------------|-------------|\n18: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Type definitions for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort, and related structs |\n19: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation with boilerplate |\n20: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` |\n21: \n22: ### Type Definitions Required\n23: \n24: #### AgentRuntime\n25: \n26: ```\n27: AgentRuntime\n28: ├── Spec\n29: │   ├── Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: targetPort)\n30: │   ├── Template (*SandboxTemplate, JSON: podTemplate, required)\n31: │   ├── SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, JSON: sessionTimeout, default: 15m)\n32: │   └── MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, JSON: maxSessionDuration, default: 8h)\n33: ├── Status\n34: │   └── Conditions ([]metav1.Condition, optional)\n35: └── List: AgentRuntimeList\n36: ```\n37: \n38: #### CodeInterpreter\n39: \n40: ```\n41: CodeInterpreter\n42: ├── Spec\n43: │   ├── Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: ports)\n44: │   ├── Template (*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, JSON: template, required)\n45: │   ├── SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, default: 15m)\n46: │   ├── MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, default: 8h)\n47: │   ├── WarmPoolSize (*int32)\n48: │   └── AuthMode (AuthModeType, default: picod, enum: picod|none)\n49: ├── Status\n50: │   ├── Conditions ([]metav1.Condition)\n51: │   └── Ready (*bool)\n52: └── List: CodeInterpreterList\n53: ```\n54: \n55: #### Supporting Types\n56: \n57: - `TargetPort`: Port configuration with optional pathPrefix/name, required port (uint32), protocol (HTTP|HTTPS)\n58: - `ProtocolType`: Enum for HTTP/HTTPS\n59: - `AuthModeType`: Enum for picod/none\n60: - `SandboxTemplate`: Labels, annotations, and embedded `corev1.PodSpec`\n61: - `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`: Image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.\n62: \n63: ### Out of Scope\n64: \n65: - Controller implementation (`pkg/controllers/`)\n66: - Webhook validation logic\n67: - CRD YAML generation (handled by `make gen-crd`)\n68: - client-go code generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n69: - HTTP API handlers (`pkg/api/`)\n70: \n71: ## Impact Analysis\n72: \n73: ### Upstream Dependencies\n74: \n75: | Dependency | Impact |\n76: |------------|--------|\n77: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required for metav1.ObjectMeta, metav1.Duration, metav1.Condition |\n78: | `k8s.io/api/corev1` | Required for embedded PodSpec in templates |\n79: \n80: ### Downstream Consumers\n81: \n82: | Consumer | Usage |\n83: |----------|-------|\n84: | `make gen-crd` | Generates CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n85: | `make gen-client` | Generates typed clients, informers, listers to `client-go/` |\n86: | Workload Manager (`cmd/workload-manager`) | Reads CRD specs to create Sandbox/SandboxClaim |\n87: | Router (`cmd/router`) | May reference CRD types for routing logic |\n88: | E2E Tests | Validates CRD creation and behavior |\n89: | Helm Chart | Ships generated CRD YAML for installation |\n90: \n91: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n92: \n93: - **Version Stability**: Using `v1alpha1` signals API instability; changes may break existing workloads\n94: - **Field Defaults**: Kubebuilder markers set defaults at CRD level; changing defaults affects existing unlabeled resources\n95: - **Enum Values**: Adding/removing enum values (ProtocolType, AuthModeType) requires CRD schema update\n96: \n97: ## Alternatives Considered\n98: \n99: ### Alternative 1: Use Unstructured CRDs\n100: \n101: **Approach**: Define CRDs via raw YAML without Go types, consume via `dynamic.Client`.\n102: \n103: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n104: |--------|------------|\n105: | Pros | No code generation dependency; faster initial setup |\n106: | Cons | No type safety; no informer/lister generation; harder validation; no IDE support |\n107: \n108: **Decision**: Rejected. AgentCube requires typed clients for controller-runtime integration and test reliability.\n109: \n110: ### Alternative 2: Single Unified CRD\n111: \n112: **Approach**: Merge AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter into one CRD with a `type` discriminator field.\n113: \n114: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n115: |--------|------------|\n116: | Pros | Fewer CRDs; simpler client-go generation |\n117: | Cons | Schema complexity; divergent status fields (`ready` only for CodeInterpreter); authMode only applies to CodeInterpreter; warmPoolSize only for CodeInterpreter |\n118: \n119: **Decision**: Rejected. The two CRDs serve distinct use cases with sufficiently different spec structures.\n120: \n121: ### Alternative 3: External Template Reference\n122: \n123: **Approach**: Use `TemplateRef` (name/namespace) instead of embedded template.\n124: \n125: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n126: |--------|------------|\n127: | Pros | Reusable templates; smaller CRD instances |\n128: | Cons | Additional lookup step; template lifecycle complexity; no inline customization |\n129: \n130: **Decision**: Rejected for initial implementation. Inline templates match agent-sandbox conventions and simplify the user experience. May consider as future extension.\n131: \n132: ### Alternative 4: Duration as int64 seconds\n133: \n134: **Approach**: Use `int64` for timeout/duration fields instead of `metav1.Duration`.\n135: \n136: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n137: |--------|------------|\n138: | Pros | Simpler serialization; no string parsing |\n139: | Cons | Non-standard K8s API; human readability reduced (e.g., \"8h\" vs 28800) |\n140: \n141: **Decision**: Rejected. `metav1.Duration` follows Kubernetes API conventions and provides human-readable defaults (\"15m\", \"8h\").\n142: \n143: ## Risks\n144: \n145: | Risk | Mitigation |\n146: |------|------------|\n147: | Kubebuilder marker typos | Run `make gen-crd` and verify output YAML |\n148: | Missing JSON tags | Use `golangci-lint` with tag-related rules |\n149: | PodSpec embedding complexity | Follow `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` patterns |\n150: | Code-generator version mismatch | Pin `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 per `hack/update-codegen.sh` |\n151: \n152: ## Implementation Notes\n153: \n154: 1. **Boilerplate**: Use `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` header via `make gen-copyright`\n155: 2. **JSON Tags**: camelCase per project conventions (e.g., `targetPort`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`)\n156: 3. **Kubebuilder Markers**: Apply `+kubebuilder:object:root`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:default`, `+kubebuilder:validation:Required`, `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum`\n157: 4. **Printer Columns**: Add `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"` for `Age` column\n158: \n159: ## References\n160: \n161: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n162: - Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n163: - agent-sandbox API: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox\n164: - Spec: `changes/AR-001/spec.md`\n165: - Client-go reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 165 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the foundational Go type structures for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These types serve as the core data model for AgentCube's sandbox orchestration platform, enabling:\n\n1. **Sandbox Template Definition**: Users define pod templates and runtime parameters via CRDs\n2. **Controller Integration**: The workload manager controller uses these types to create/manage `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` resources\n3. **Client Generation**: These types are the source for `k8s.io/code-generator` to produce typed clients, informers, and listers (see `deployment/client-go.md`)\n4. **Helm Chart CRDs**: `controller-gen` generates CRD YAML from these types (see `manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Type definitions for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort, and related structs |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation with boilerplate |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775847814991,"end":1775847815002}}}}
