{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775847822586,"sessionID":"ses_2873b7541ffeDi6b2Lu8gh0Fzw","part":{"id":"prt_d78c754f7001FFnHvB6tF14LA0","messageID":"msg_d78c73787001pHO4Fm8pS1h52f","sessionID":"ses_2873b7541ffeDi6b2Lu8gh0Fzw","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775847876976,"sessionID":"ses_2873b7541ffeDi6b2Lu8gh0Fzw","part":{"id":"prt_d78c778d0001LJQIuKD3RFgEsh","messageID":"msg_d78c73787001pHO4Fm8pS1h52f","sessionID":"ses_2873b7541ffeDi6b2Lu8gh0Fzw","type":"text","text":"Now I have the complete understanding of the codebase and proposal format. Let me write the proposal for AR-008.","time":{"start":1775847876973,"end":1775847876973}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847877070,"sessionID":"ses_2873b7541ffeDi6b2Lu8gh0Fzw","part":{"id":"prt_d78c82971001XF363lNLnCshpC","messageID":"msg_d78c73787001pHO4Fm8pS1h52f","sessionID":"ses_2873b7541ffeDi6b2Lu8gh0Fzw","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-7ee28c4ec3e5413d916bcb1ae08094ce","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/proposal.md","content":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement a time-based garbage collection mechanism for Sandbox resources in the Workload Manager. This ensures automatic cleanup of expired and idle sandboxes, preventing resource accumulation and cluster bloat. The GC mechanism provides:\n\n1. **TTL Enforcement**: Automatically deletes sandboxes that exceed their `ExpiresAt` timestamp\n2. **Idle Timeout Cleanup**: Removes sandboxes with no activity beyond the configured idle timeout\n3. **Batch Processing**: Limits cleanup operations per cycle to avoid overwhelming the cluster\n4. **Configurable Intervals**: Adjustable GC cycle and idle timeout durations\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | GarbageCollector struct with Start/Stop lifecycle, runLoop, runOnce methods |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | Unit tests for GC behavior (expired, inactive, batch limits, concurrency) |\n| `Store interface extensions` | `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` and `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` methods |\n| `GarbageCollectorStats` | Runtime statistics retrieval (Interval, OnceTimeout, IdleTimeout) |\n| `SetIdleTimeout` | Dynamic idle timeout configuration at runtime |\n\n### Key Components\n\n```\nGarbageCollector\n├── Configuration\n│   ├── interval (time.Duration, default: 2m)\n│   ├── onceTimeout (time.Duration, default: 2m)\n│   └── idleTimeout (time.Duration, default: 15m)\n├── Lifecycle\n│   ├── Start() - launches background runLoop goroutine\n│   ├── Stop() - graceful shutdown via stopCh\n│   └── runLoop() - ticker-driven periodic execution\n├── Cleanup Logic\n│   ├── runOnce(ctx) - single GC cycle\n│   ├── ListExpiredSandboxes - query expired by ExpiresAt\n│   ├── ListInactiveSandboxes - query idle by LastActivity\n│   └── Batch deletion (limit: GCBatchSize=16)\n└── Runtime Config\n│   ├── SetIdleTimeout(timeout)\n│   └── GetStats() → GarbageCollectorStats\n```\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Kubernetes CronJob-based GC (alternative approach, not selected)\n- Webhook-triggered cleanup\n- Manual deletion APIs (covered by AR-xxx handlers)\n- GC metrics/ Prometheus export (future enhancement)\n- Distributed GC coordination across multiple workload-manager instances\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Impact |\n|------------|--------|\n| `SandboxLifecycleManager` | GC delegates deletion via `DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` |\n| `Store` interface | Requires `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` implementations |\n| `MemoryStore` | In-memory implementation with expiration/activity indexes |\n| `time.Ticker` | Standard library ticker for periodic execution |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | DeleteOptions for K8s resource cleanup |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| `HTTPServer` | Creates and manages GC lifecycle in `NewHTTPServerWithClients` |\n| `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox` | GC invokes this for each cleanup target |\n| `MemoryStore` | Provides sandbox listing for expired/inactive queries |\n| `Integration tests` | Verify GC behavior under concurrent load |\n\n### Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **Store Interface Extension**: Adding `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` to Store interface requires all implementations to provide these methods\n- **Default Idle Timeout**: Changing `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` affects existing sandboxes without explicit timeout annotation\n- **GC Interval**: Modifying `GarbageCollectorInterval` impacts cleanup frequency and cluster load\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Kubernetes CronJob-based GC\n\n**Approach**: Deploy a CronJob that runs periodically to scan and delete expired sandboxes.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Native Kubernetes scheduling; decoupled from workload-manager; easier horizontal scaling |\n| Cons | Additional RBAC permissions; delayed cleanup (cron schedule granularity); no idle timeout support; requires separate deployment |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. In-process GC provides immediate cleanup after TTL expiry, tighter integration with lifecycle management, and idle timeout handling that CronJob cannot efficiently implement.\n\n### Alternative 2: Event-driven Cleanup (Webhook)\n\n**Approach**: Use Kubernetes admission webhook or event handler to trigger cleanup on resource changes.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Real-time cleanup; no periodic scanning overhead |\n| Cons | Complex webhook setup; requires watch on all Sandbox resources; cannot handle idle timeout without additional state |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Timer-based GC is simpler, covers both TTL and idle timeout cases, and matches the workload-manager's controller-like architecture.\n\n### Alternative 3: TTL Controller Delegation\n\n**Approach**: Use Kubernetes TTL controller (built-in for Jobs/Pods) or custom controller for cleanup.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Native controller pattern; standard K8s mechanisms |\n| Cons | TTL controller doesn't support custom resources; idle timeout not part of TTL spec |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter are custom CRDs; built-in TTL controller doesn't support them. Custom TTL annotation handling requires in-process logic.\n\n### Alternative 4: Distributed GC with Leader Election\n\n**Approach**: Multiple workload-manager instances coordinate cleanup via leader election.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | High availability; prevents duplicate deletions |\n| Cons | Complexity; requires lease management; adds coordination overhead for S-size task |\n\n**Decision**: Deferred. Current single-instance GC suffices for initial implementation. Leader election can be added when HA deployment is required.\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| GC overload during peak sandbox count | Batch limit (GCBatchSize=16) throttles deletions per cycle |\n| Concurrent runOnce calls race condition | `runOnce` is only called from single goroutine; store uses mutex protection |\n| GC stuck on slow deletion | `onceTimeout` limits total GC cycle duration; individual deletions have `DeletionTimeout` |\n| MemoryStore query performance with large sandbox count | In-memory index; sorted by expiry/activity time; limit truncates results |\n| Missing LastActivity updates | Ensure activity tracking in sandbox creation/heartbeat handlers |\n| GC stops unexpectedly | `Stop()` waits for goroutine completion via `sync.WaitGroup` |\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Constants**: `GCBatchSize = 16`, `GarbageCollectorInterval = 2 * time.Minute`\n2. **Deletion Flow**: GC calls `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox` which handles both K8s CR deletion and store cleanup\n3. **Reason Tracking**: `determineDeletionReason` categorizes deletions as `IdleTimeout`, `MaxDurationReached`, or `UserRequest`\n4. **Error Handling**: NotFound errors are ignored (already deleted); other errors logged but don't stop GC cycle\n5. **Configurable Idle Timeout**: `SetIdleTimeout` allows runtime adjustment via HTTP API (future)\n6. **Test Coverage**: Unit tests verify expired/inactive cleanup, batch limits, concurrent safety\n\n## References\n\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - Implementation\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` - Test coverage\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` - DeleteSandbox delegation\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` - ListExpiredSandboxes/ListInactiveSandboxes\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` - Default timeout constants\n- Kubernetes TTL Controller: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/ttlafterfinished/"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/config.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":49,"character":49},"end":{"line":49,"character":60}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"k8s.io/utils should be direct"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":37,"character":14},"end":{"line":37,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field WriteTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":13},"end":{"line":38,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field IdleTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":39,"character":17},"end":{"line":39,"character":17}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field ShutdownTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":40,"character":15},"end":{"line":40,"character":15}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field EnableHealthz"},{"range":{"start":{"line":41,"character":14},"end":{"line":41,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field EnableReadyz"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/common/types/sandbox.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":60,"character":40},"end":{"line":60,"character":71}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#omitzero"},"source":"omitzero","message":"Omitempty has no effect on nested struct fields"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":239,"character":5},"end":{"line":239,"character":24}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#rangeint"},"source":"rangeint","message":"for loop can be modernized using range over int"},{"range":{"start":{"line":283,"character":5},"end":{"line":283,"character":23}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/moderni